aaaXmlOn.description: Set to 1 to enable AAA XML Interface, 0 to disable. Note: If trying to set this value returns an error, please check to see if you have a valid license for this feature.

aaaXmlSender1Ip.description: IP address of the first server that will send/process XML commands for subscriber management.

authSubCountDown.name: authSubCountDown
authSubCountDown.description: Set to 1 to enable count-down after login for a subscriber, 0 to disable. Note: username and password should have been entered before, in order to enable this option. Also, expiration time must be entered after enabling this option, in order for it to work properly.

authSubUser1.description: Optional field. Used for simple notations about the subscriber.

authSubUser2.description: Optional field. Used for simple notations about the subscriber.

lpfEntryOnlineStatus.name: lpfEntryOnlineStatus
lpfEntryOnlineStatus.description: Status of an External Login Page server.

radHistSysloggingOn.name: radHistSysloggingOn
radHistSysloggingOn.description: Setting this value to (1) will enable logging (via standard SYSLOG) of RADIUS packets. Setting this value to (0) will disable RADIUS history logging. (NOTE: Which types of RADIUS packets will be logged is specified using other parameters.)

radHistSyslogNumber.name: radHistSyslogNumber
radHistSyslogNumber.description: The log number (0-7 of standard SYSLOG) for AAA logging.

radHistSyslogFilter.name: radHistSyslogFilter
radHistSyslogFilter.description: Select the filter level for RADIUS History Logs Available settings: Emergency(0), Alert(1), Critical(2), Error(3), Warning(4), Notice(5), Info(6), Debug(7)

radHistSyslogServerIp.name: radHistSyslogServerIp
radHistSyslogServerIp.description: IP address of the SYSLOG server to receive AAA messages.

radHistSyslogSaveToFile.name: radHistSyslogSaveToFile
radHistSyslogSaveToFile.description: Setting this value to (1) will enable saving of RADIUS History logs to file. Setting this value to (0) will disable storing of AAA logs in a file.

radProxyAcctHistLog.name: radProxyAcctHistLog
radProxyAcctHistLog.description: Setting this value to (1) enables the logging of RADIUS Proxy Accounting packets to a logfile on the system flash. Setting it to zero disables such logging and purges the history logfile.

radProxyAcctHistSyslog.name: radProxyAcctHistSyslog
radProxyAcctHistSyslog.description: If RADIUS History Syslogging is enabled, then setting this value to (1) causes RADIUS Proxy accounting packets to be included in that syslogging. Setting it to zero causes these packets not to be included.

aaaRadiusRoutingMode.name: aaaRadiusRoutingMode
aaaRadiusRoutingMode.description: Set to 0 to disable radius client operation. Set to 1 to enable realm-based routing of RADIUS requests. Set to 2 to route all RADIUS requests to the default RADIUS service profile. Note: If trying to set this value returns an error, please check to see if you have a valid license for this feature.

aaaRadiusDefProf.name: aaaRadiusDefProf
aaaRadiusDefProf.description: Set the default RADIUS service profile to be used for otherwise un-routeable RADIUS requests. Mandatory if the routing mode is set to fixed. There must be a profile defined with the specified name.

aaaRadiusCacheOn.name: aaaRadiusCacheOn
aaaRadiusCacheOn.description: Set to 1 to enable radius profile caching, 0 to disable.

aaaRadiusDefaultIdle.name: aaaRadiusDefaultIdle
aaaRadiusDefaultIdle.description: Set default timeout for radius subscribers.

aaaRadiusNasIdOn.name: aaaRadiusNasIdOn
aaaRadiusNasIdOn.description: Set to 1 to Send NAS ID, 0 to disable.

aaaRadiusNasIpOn.name: aaaRadiusNasIpOn
aaaRadiusNasIpOn.description: Set to 1 to Send NAS IP, 0 to disable.

aaaRadiusNasPortOn.name: aaaRadiusNasPortOn
aaaRadiusNasPortOn.description: Set to 1 to Send NAS Port Type, 0 to disable.

aaaRadiusFipOn.name: aaaRadiusFipOn
aaaRadiusFipOn.description: Set to 1 to Send Frame IP, 0 to disable.

aaaRadiusRedUrlOn.name: aaaRadiusRedUrlOn
aaaRadiusRedUrlOn.description: Set to 1 to support URL redirection, 0 to disable.

aaaRadiusGoodbyeUrlOn.name: aaaRadiusGoodbyeUrlOn
aaaRadiusGoodbyeUrlOn.description: Set to 1 to support Goodbye URL redirection, 0 to disable.

aaaRadiusForgotPasswordUrlOn.name: aaaRadiusForgotPasswordUrlOn
aaaRadiusForgotPasswordUrlOn.description: Set to 1 to support forgot password URL redirection, 0 to disable.

aaaRadiusForgotPasswordUrl.name: aaaRadiusForgotPasswordUrl
aaaRadiusForgotPasswordUrl.description: URL of the RADIUS Forgot Password

aaaRadiusSubnetAttrOn.name: aaaRadiusSubnetAttrOn
aaaRadiusSubnetAttrOn.description: Set to 1 to support subnet attribute, 0 to disable.

aaaRadiusNetVlanOn.name: aaaRadiusNetVlanOn
aaaRadiusNetVlanOn.description: Set to 1 to enable, 0 to disable RADIUS based WAN VLAN. Note: enabling RADIUS based WAN VLAN will automatically disable SSID based WAN VLAN.

aaaRadiusNetVlanDefaultOn.name: aaaRadiusNetVlanDefaultOn
aaaRadiusNetVlanDefaultOn.description: Set to 1 to enable default 802.1q tag for system traffic, 0 to disable.

aaaRadiusNetVlanDefaultTag.name: aaaRadiusNetVlanDefaultTag
aaaRadiusNetVlanDefaultTag.description: Set the default 802.1q tag for system traffic.

aaaRadiusLocalAuthPort.name: aaaRadiusLocalAuthPort
aaaRadiusLocalAuthPort.description: Local UDP port for communicating with authentication servers. Must be either 0 or in the range 1024-5000.

aaaRadiusLocalAcctPort.name: aaaRadiusLocalAcctPort
aaaRadiusLocalAcctPort.description: Local UDP port for communicating with accounting servers. Must be either 0 or in the range 1024-5000.

aaaRadiusLoginRefresh.name: aaaRadiusLoginRefresh
aaaRadiusLoginRefresh.description: Login refresh time for RADIUS subscribers

aaaRadiusTerminationActionOn.name: aaaRadiusTerminationActionOn
aaaRadiusTerminationActionOn.description: Set to 1 to support Termination-Action attribute, 0 to disable.

blockTelnetAccessOn.name: blockTelnetAccessOn
blockTelnetAccessOn.description: Set to 1 to enable blocking of all Telnet access, 0 to disable. Note: if set to 1, Telnet access will not be allowed, even from addresses in the access control IP Table.

blockWebAccessOn.name: blockWebAccessOn
blockWebAccessOn.description: Set to 1 to enable blocking of all Web access, 0 to disable. Note: if set to 1, Web access will not be allowed, even from addresses in the access control IP Table.

blockFtpAccessOn.name: blockFtpAccessOn
blockFtpAccessOn.description: Set to 1 to enable blocking of all FTP access, 0 to disable. Note: if set to 1, FTP access will not be allowed, even from addresses in the access control IP Table.

accessControlOn.name: accessControlOn
accessControlOn.description: Set to 1 to enable Source IP Access Control, 0 to disable. Note: If trying to set this value returns an error, please check to see if you have a valid license for this feature.

acStartAddress.description: Access Control range Starting IP address

acEndAddress.name: acEndAddress
acEndAddress.description: Access Control range end IP address

acStatus.name: acStatus

blockSFTPAccessOn.name: blockSFTPAccessOn
blockSFTPAccessOn.description: Set to 1 to enable blocking of all SFTP access, 0 to disable. Note: if set to 1, SFTP access will not be allowed, even from addresses in the access control IP Table.

blockSSHShellAccessOn.name: blockSSHShellAccessOn
blockSSHShellAccessOn.description: Set to 1 to enable blocking of all SSH Shell access, 0 to disable. Note: if set to 1, SSH Shell access will not be allowed, even from addresses in the access control IP Table.

bandwidthManagementOn.name: bandwidthManagementOn
bandwidthManagementOn.description: Set to 1 to enable Bandwidth Management, 0 to disable. Note: If trying to set this value returns an error, please check to see if you have a valid license for this feature. Note: You must reboot for changes to take effect.

bwmUpWanLinkSpeed.name: bwmUpWanLinkSpeed

bwmDownWanLinkSpeed.name: bwmDownWanLinkSpeed
bwmDownWanLinkSpeed.description: Downlink Bandwidth through the Network's WAN link to control using Bandwidth Management. Note: You must reboot for changes to take effect.

brmMirrorOn.name: brmMirrorOn
brmMirrorOn.description: Setting this value to (1) will cause Bill Record Mirroring to be enabled by this unit. Setting this value to (0) will disable Bill Record Mirroring. Note: If trying to set this value returns an error, please check to see if you have a valid license for this feature.

dhcpDisable.name: dhcpDisable
dhcpDisable.description: Set to true to disable DHCP services. This variable returns false when one of the DHCP services is enabled through either dhcpIpUpsell, dhcpServerEnable or dhcpRelayEnable. Note: You must reboot for changes to take effect.

dhcpIpUpsell.name: dhcpIpUpsell
dhcpIpUpsell.description: Set to 0 to disable public IP Upsell service, 1 to enable public IP Upsell. Requires SUBNET to be enabled. Make sure you have a valid license for this feature; otherwise, an error will be returned when trying to set. Please reboot for the changes to take effect.

dhcpServerEnable.name: dhcpServerEnable
dhcpServerEnable.description: Set to 0 to disable DHCP service, 1 to enable DHCP server. Note: You must reboot for changes to take effect.

dhcpServerSubnetBased.name: dhcpServerSubnetBased
dhcpServerSubnetBased.description: Set to 0 to disable subnet-based DHCP service, 1 to enable subnet-based DHCP service. Note: You must reboot for changes to take effect.

serverIp.name: serverIp
serverIp.description: IP Address to bind to the internal DHCP Server. Note: You must reboot for changes to take effect.

netMask.name: netMask
netMask.description: DHCP Server subnet mask. Note: You must reboot for changes to take effect.

poolStartIp.name: poolStartIp
poolStartIp.description: Starting IP address of DHCP lease pool. Note: You must reboot for changes to take effect.

poolStopIp.name: poolStopIp
poolStopIp.description: Ending IP address of DHCP lease pool. Note: You must reboot for changes to take effect.

leaseMinutes.name: leaseMinutes
leaseMinutes.description: DHCP lease duration in minutes. Note: You must reboot for changes to take effect.

ipUpSell.name: ipUpSell
ipUpSell.description: IP pool used for IP Upsell

defaultPool.name: defaultPool
defaultPool.description: IP pool is the default pool

poolStatus.name: poolStatus
poolStatus.description: Status of the DHCP pool table entry.

leaseCLID.description: Client ID of subscriber to whom lease is assigned

leaseStatus.name: leaseStatus
leaseStatus.description: Status of the lease (available or reserved)

dhcpRelayEnable.name: dhcpRelayEnable
dhcpRelayEnable.description: Set to 0 to disable DHCP Relay service, 1 to enable DHCP Relay service. Note: You must reboot for changes to take effect.

dhcpRelayAgentIP.name: dhcpRelayAgentIP
dhcpRelayAgentIP.description: IP Address of the Relay Agent. Note: You must reboot for changes to take effect.

dhcpRelayServerIP.name: dhcpRelayServerIP
dhcpRelayServerIP.description: IP Address to which the Relay Agent will forward subscriber DHCP requests. Note: You must reboot for changes to take effect.

dnsHostName.description: DNS Hostname. Note: You must reboot for changes to take effect.

dnsDomain.description: DNS domain. Note: In order to set this value, DHCP Client must be disabled. Note: You must reboot for changes to take effect.

dnsPrimaryServer.name: dnsPrimaryServer
dnsPrimaryServer.description: Primary DNS Server. Note: In order to set this value, both DHCP Client and PPPoE Client must be disabled. Note: You must reboot for changes to take effect.

dnsSecondaryServer.name: dnsSecondaryServer
dnsSecondaryServer.description: Secondary DNS Server. Note: In order to set this value, both DHCP Client and PPPoE Client must be disabled. Note: You must reboot for changes to take effect.

dnsTertiaryServer.name: dnsTertiaryServer
dnsTertiaryServer.description: Tertiary DNS Server. Note: You must reboot for changes to take effect.

dynDnsEnable.name: dynDnsEnable
dynDnsEnable.description: Set to 0 to disable Dynamic DNS, 1 to enable Dynamic DNS

dynDnsProtocol.name: dynDnsProtocol
dynDnsProtocol.description: Set to 0 to set protocol to dyndns.org, or set protocol to 1 to set it to dyndns.org (secure) protocol

dynDnsServer.name: dynDnsServer
dynDnsServer.description: Server name given by dynamic DNS provider. Please specify only domain name, without http://, '/', etc

dynDnsPort.name: dynDnsPort
dynDnsPort.description: Set port on which to connect to dynamic dns provider. NOTE: port 443 may only be chosen if protocol is dynDnsOrgProtoSecure (dyndns.org (secure)). For non-secure version of dyndns.org protocol: set to 0 for port 80; set to 1 for port 8245. For secure version: set port to 443

dynDnsHostname.name: dynDnsHostname
dynDnsHostname.description: Hostname which ip address of the NSE will be mapped to. Please specify only domain name, without http://, '/', etc

dynDnsUsername.name: dynDnsUsername
dynDnsUsername.description: Username associated with dynamic dns account

dynDnsPassword.name: dynDnsPassword
dynDnsPassword.description: Password associated with dynamic dns account.

dynDnsForceUpdate.name: dynDnsForceUpdate
dynDnsForceUpdate.description: When set to 1 will perform a forced dynamic DNS update. When set to false will have no effect. Will always return 0 on get. IMPORTANT: some Dynamic DNS Providers (e.g. dyndns.org) consider unnecessary updates (i.e. updates with unchanged IP addresses) abusive. Such updates may result in hostname / username being blocked.

greTunnelingEnable.name: greTunnelingEnable
greTunnelingEnable.description: Set to 0 to disable GRE Tunneling service, 1 to enable GRE Tunneling service. Note: you must reboot for changes to take effect.

greVpnConcentratorIp.name: greVpnConcentratorIp
greVpnConcentratorIp.description: IP Address of the VPN Concentrator Server. Note: you must reboot for changes to take effect.

greInterfaceIp.name: greInterfaceIp
greInterfaceIp.description: IP Address of the GRE Interface on this device. Note: you must reboot for changes to take effect.

greInterfaceNetmask.name: greInterfaceNetmask
greInterfaceNetmask.description: The Subnet Mask for the GRE Interface on this device. Note: you must reboot for changes to take effect.

greInterfaceGateway.name: greInterfaceGateway
greInterfaceGateway.description: The Gateway for the GRE Interface on this device. Note: you must reboot for changes to take effect.

hprOn.description: Setting this value to (1) will cause home page redirection to be performed by this unit. Setting this value to (0) will discontinue HPR. Note: If trying to set this value returns an error, please check to see if you have a valid license for this feature.

hprUrl.name: hprUrl
hprUrl.description: The fully qualified WWW URL at which to redirect Home Page Requests.

hprParameterPassing.name: hprParameterPassing
hprParameterPassing.description: Setting this value to (1) will cause inclusion of parameters with the passed URL during HPR. Setting this value to (0) will discontinue parameter passing.

hprRedirectionFrequency.name: hprRedirectionFrequency
hprRedirectionFrequency.description: The time interval, specified in minutes, after which the next redirection will take place.

iccOn.name: iccOn
iccOn.description: Set to (1) to enable the ICC. Set to (0) to disable. Note: If trying to set this value returns an error, please check to see if you have a valid license for this feature.

iccTitle.name: iccTitle
iccTitle.description: The title to appear on the ICC console window

iccLogoutOption.name: iccLogoutOption
iccLogoutOption.description: What should the ICC do when a subscriber closes it? 0 to Redisplay, 2 to logout and return the user to a *Pending* state (valid only with RADIUS)

iccLanguageOption.name: iccLanguageOption
iccLanguageOption.description: What language would you like to be displayed on the ICC? Available settings: 0=English, 1=Chinese, 2=French, 3=German, 4=Japanese, 5=Spanish, 6=Other. If *other* is selected, please make a selection for iccCharSetOption.

iccTimerOption.name: iccTimerOption
iccTimerOption.description: Set to (1) for ICC Elapsed Time. Set to (0) for Time Remaining. Note: If trying to set this value returns an error, please check to see if you have a valid license for this feature.

iccCharSetOption.description: This value indicates specific character set to be displayed. In order to set this value, iccLanguageOption should be first set to *other*. Available settings: 0=default, 1=western-iso-8859-1, 2=chinese-big5, 3=chinese-euc-cn, 4=chinese-euc-tw, 5=chinese-gb2312, 6=japanese-euc-jp, 7=japanese-iso-2022-jp, 8=japanese-shift-jis, 9=korean-euc-kr, 10=korean-iso-2022-kr, 11=korean-ks-c-5601.

iccBannerDuration1.name: iccBannerDuration1
iccBannerDuration1.description: ICC Banner 1 Duration in seconds. Minimum allowed value is 30.

iccBannerDuration2.name: iccBannerDuration2
iccBannerDuration2.description: ICC Banner 2 Duration in seconds. Minimum allowed value is 30.

iccBannerDuration3.name: iccBannerDuration3
iccBannerDuration3.description: ICC Banner 3 Duration in seconds. Minimum allowed value is 30.

iccBannerDuration4.name: iccBannerDuration4
iccBannerDuration4.description: ICC Banner 4 Duration in seconds. Minimum allowed value is 30.

iccBannerDuration5.name: iccBannerDuration5
iccBannerDuration5.description: ICC Banner 5 Duration in seconds. Minimum allowed value is 30.

inatOn.description: Set to 1 to enable iNAT, 0 to disable. Valid License is required

pptpOn.name: pptpOn
pptpOn.description: Set to 1 to enable PPTP, 0 to disable. Valid License is required

pptpidOn.name: pptpidOn
pptpidOn.description: Set to 1 to enable PPTP ID support, 0 to disable. Valid PPTP License is required Note: You must reboot for changes to take effect.

ipsecOn.name: ipsecOn
ipsecOn.description: Set to 1 to enable subscriber IPSec passthru, 0 to disable. Valid License is required. (NOTE: This is not to be confused with the MIB variable ipsecVpnOn, which pertains to IPSec traffic between the NSE and remote hosts).

inatEntryStatus.name: inatEntryStatus
inatEntryStatus.description: Status of the iNAT table entry.

lkFeatureList.name: lkFeatureList
lkFeatureList.description: List of features using the license key.

locationVenueType.name: locationVenueType
locationVenueType.description: This value indicates Venue Type chosen: (1) Apartment (2) Bar/Coffeeshop/Restaurant (3) Convention Center (4) Corporate Guest Access (5) Education (6) Hospitality (7) Marina/camp ground (8) Public Space (9) Public transport (10) Other

locationGateway.name: locationGateway
locationGateway.description: The IP Address of the default gateway. Note: in order to set this value, locationNetIntfCfgMode must be set to static. Note: you must reboot for changes to take effect.

locationNetIntfCfgMode.name: locationNetIntfCfgMode
locationNetIntfCfgMode.description: Setting this value to (0) will use statically configured IP address. Setting to (1) will enable DHCP Client for the system. Setting to (2) will enable PPPoE Client for the system. Note: you must reboot for changes to take effect.

passthroughOn.name: passthroughOn
passthroughOn.description: Setting this value to (1) will enable Passthrough Addresses feature. Setting this value to (0) will disable it. Note: If trying to set this value returns an error, please check to see if you have a valid license for this feature.

passthroughIPTable.description: Host passthrough table for IP addresses

passthroughname.description: The packets destined for this DNS name are passed through without authentication, authorization.

portLocInRoomPortMappingOn.description: Setting this value to (1) will enable In Room Port Mapping feature. Setting this value to (0) will disable this feature. Note: If trying to set this value returns an error, please check to see if you have a valid license for this feature.

portLocConcentratorType.name: portLocConcentratorType
portLocConcentratorType.description: Setting this value to (0) will indicate that no concentrator will be used. Entering (1) will mean the device which understands 802.1Q VLAN IDs one-way will be used, while (2) will indicate the device which understands 802.1Q VLAN IDs two-ways. Entering (3) to (8) will indicate that one of the following access concentrators will be exploited: (3) Tut Systems Expresso, (4) Lucent DSL Terminator, (5) Tut MDU Lite Systems, (6) any RFC1493 Compliant System, (7) RiverDelta 1000B, (8) Elastic Networks.

portLocConcentratorTable.name: portLocConcentratorTable
portLocConcentratorTable.description: List of IP addresses, SNMP community names, and uplink ports for each concentrator.

portLocTableEntry.description: One entry of the port-location table

portLocPort.name: portLocPort
portLocPort.description: Port of the concentrator this room is connected to

portLocModemMAC.name: portLocModemMAC
portLocModemMAC.description: MAC Address of the Modem this room has (valid for Riverdelta and similar concentrators only)

radProxyServices.description: Setting this value to (1) enables RADIUS proxy services. Setting it to zero disables RADIUS proxy services.

radProxyAcctSvrPort.name: radProxyAcctSvrPort
radProxyAcctSvrPort.description: The UDP port number on which RADIUS accounting requests will be received. Setting this value to (0) disables RADIUS accounting proxy services.

radProxyLocalServcomPort.name: radProxyLocalServcomPort
radProxyLocalServcomPort.description: Local UDP port for communicating with downstream servers. Must be either 0 or in the range 1024-5000.

nasIpAddress.name: nasIpAddress
nasIpAddress.description: IP Address of the upstream NAS.

nasAcctSec.name: nasAcctSec
nasAcctSec.description: The secret key, shared with the upstream NAS, used for accounting packets.

nasDefProf.name: nasDefProf
nasDefProf.description: (Optional) The name of the RADIUS service profile to handle requests from this upstream NAS if realm-basd routing fails. If not present, such packets will be discarded.

nasStatus.description: Status of the upstream NAS table entry.

serviceProfileTableEntry.description: An entry in the list of service profiles.

profName.name: profName

radAuthOn.description: Set to 1 to enable radius authentication for this profile, 0 to disable.

radAuthProto.description: Radius authentication protocol: rad-auth-proto-pap(0) - PAP rad-auth-proto-chap(1) - CHAP-MD5 rad-auth-proto-mschap-v1(2) - MS-CHAP v1 rad-auth-proto-mschap-v2(3) - MS-CHAP v2

radAuthSrv1Ip.description: IP address of the Primary Radius Authentication Server for this profile.

radAuthSrv1Sec.description: Secret Key of the Primary Radius Authentication Server for this profile.

radAuthSrv2Ip.name: radAuthSrv2Ip
radAuthSrv2Ip.description: IP address of the Secondary Radius Authentication Server for this profile.

radAuthSrv2Port.name: radAuthSrv2Port
radAuthSrv2Port.description: Port of the Secondary Radius Authentication Server for this profile.

radAuthSrv2Sec.name: radAuthSrv2Sec
radAuthSrv2Sec.description: Secret Key of the Secondary Radius Authentication Server for this profile.

radAcctOn.name: radAcctOn
radAcctOn.description: Set to 1 to enable radius accounting for this profile, 0 to disable.

radAcctSrv1Ip.name: radAcctSrv1Ip
radAcctSrv1Ip.description: IP address of the Primary Radius Accounting Server for this profile.

radAcctSrv1Port.name: radAcctSrv1Port
radAcctSrv1Port.description: Port of the Primary Radius Accounting Server for this profile.

radAcctSrv1Sec.name: radAcctSrv1Sec
radAcctSrv1Sec.description: Secret Key of the Primary Radius Accounting Server for this profile.

radAcctSrv2Ip.name: radAcctSrv2Ip
radAcctSrv2Ip.description: IP address of the Secondary Radius Accounting Server for this profile.

radAcctSrv2Port.name: radAcctSrv2Port
radAcctSrv2Port.description: Port of the Secondary Radius Accounting Server for this profile.

radAcctSrv2Sec.name: radAcctSrv2Sec
radAcctSrv2Sec.description: Secret Key of the Secondary Radius Accounting Server for this profile.

radRetrMethod.name: radRetrMethod
radRetrMethod.description: Set to 0 if the retransmission method is failover, 1 if round-robin.

radRetrFreq.name: radRetrFreq
radRetrFreq.description: Set the frequency of retransmission (per second).

profStatus.name: profStatus
profStatus.description: Status of the service profile table entry.

tunnelProfileTableEntry.name: tunnelProfileTableEntry
tunnelProfileTableEntry.description: An entry in the list of tunnel profiles.

tunProfName.name: tunProfName
tunProfName.description: The name of this tunnel profile. Must be unique.

tunPeerIp.name: tunPeerIp
tunPeerIp.description: IP address of the tunnel peer for this tunnel.

tunProfStatus.name: tunProfStatus
tunProfStatus.description: Status of the tunnel profile table entry.

realmBasedRoutingTableEntry.name: realmBasedRoutingTableEntry
realmBasedRoutingTableEntry.description: An entry in the list of realm-based routes.

realmEntryActive.name: realmEntryActive
realmEntryActive.description: Indicates whether or not this route is active.

realmWildcard.name: realmWildcard
realmWildcard.description: Indicates whether or not this route will match all realm-names or a single, specific realm-name.

realmName.name: realmName
realmName.description: If this route is for a specific realm, this is the name of that realm.

realmMatchType.name: realmMatchType
realmMatchType.description: Indicates whether this policy pertains to prefix realms, suffix realms, or to both.

realmProfile.name: realmProfile
realmProfile.description: The RADIUS service profile to which this policy will route.

realmTunProfile.name: realmTunProfile
realmTunProfile.description: The tunnel profile to which this policy will route.

realmStrip.name: realmStrip
realmStrip.description: Indicates whether or not realm-names should be stripped from user names before sending the username to a RADIUS server.

realmTunStrip.name: realmTunStrip
realmTunStrip.description: Indicates whether or not realm-names should be stripped from user names before sending the username to a tunnel server (LNS).

realmTunLocHostName.name: realmTunLocHostName
realmTunLocHostName.description: Local host name fopr purposes of tunnels, whether profile-triggerred or RADIUS-triggerred

realmStatus.name: realmStatus
realmStatus.description: Status of the realm-based routing table entry.

sessionLimitMeanRate.name: sessionLimitMeanRate
sessionLimitMeanRate.description: This value indicates the session rate limiting mean rate. THE VALUE MUST BE LESS THAN the session rate limiting burst size.

sessionLimitBurstSize.name: sessionLimitBurstSize
sessionLimitBurstSize.description: This value indicates the session rate burst size. THE VALUE MUST BE LARGER THAN the session rate limiting mean rate

sessionLimitTimeInterval.name: sessionLimitTimeInterval
sessionLimitTimeInterval.description: This value indicates the session rate time interval.

sessionLimitFilterOffendersEnable.name: sessionLimitFilterOffendersEnable
sessionLimitFilterOffendersEnable.description: Enable/Disable adding users who exceed prescribed rate to MAC Filtering

smtpRedirect.name: smtpRedirect
smtpRedirect.description: Setting this value to (1) enables SMTP redirection for misconfigured subscribers. Setting this value to (0) disables SMTP redirection for misconfigured subscribers. (NOTE: Setting it to (0) also sets it to (0) for properly configureds).

smtpServerIP.name: smtpServerIP
smtpServerIP.description: The IP address of the SMTP server to redirect all SMTP messages to.

smtpPcRedirect.name: smtpPcRedirect
smtpPcRedirect.description: Setting this value to (1) enables SMTP redirection for properly configured subscribers. Setting this value to (0) disables SMTP redirection for properly configured subscribers. (NOTE: Setting it to (1) also sets it to (1) for mis-configureds).

smtpUsername.name: smtpUsername
smtpUsername.description: For SMTP servers which support login authentication, enter valid username for an account on that server. NOTE: Length of username should be shortest allowed by SMTP server. Clients with shorter username may not be able to send e-mail.

smtpPassword.name: smtpPassword
smtpPassword.description: For SMTP servers which support login authentication, enter valid password for an account on that server. NOTE: Length of username should be shortest allowed by SMTP server. Clients with shorter password may not be able to send e-mail.

smtpServerDNS.name: smtpServerDNS
smtpServerDNS.description: The DNS name of the SMTP server to redirect all SMTP messages to. If this field is set, then smtpServerIP will also be updated to reflect the resolved IP address of the DNS name.

snmpdOn.name: snmpdOn
snmpdOn.description: Set to 1 to enable SNMP, 0 to disable. Note: If trying to set this value returns an error, please check to see if you have a valid license for this feature. Note: You must reboot for changes to take effect.

systemContact.name: systemContact
systemContact.description: System contact person. Note: You must reboot for changes to take effect.

systemLocation.name: systemLocation
systemLocation.description: Physical location of this device. Note: You must reboot for changes to take effect.

getCommunity.name: getCommunity
getCommunity.description: Get community string. Note: You must reboot for changes to take effect.

setCommunity.name: setCommunity
setCommunity.description: Set community string. Note: You must reboot for changes to take effect.

trapCommunity.name: trapCommunity
trapCommunity.description: Trap community string. Note: You must reboot for changes to take effect.

trapIP.name: trapIP
trapIP.description: IP address of host to which to send traps. Note: You must reboot for changes to take effect.

subnetStatus.name: subnetStatus
subnetStatus.description: Status of the public subnet table entry.

subIdleLogoutTimeout.name: subIdleLogoutTimeout
subIdleLogoutTimeout.description: Time (in seconds), after which subscriber is logged out. Does not apply to subscribers logged in via RADIUS. Valid values are from 300 to 86400 seconds

subToSubCommBlock.name: subToSubCommBlock
subToSubCommBlock.description: When enabled, this feature will prevent wireless subscribers from communicating with one another. When communications blocking is disabled, subscribers will be allowed to communicate

systemLoggingOn.name: systemLoggingOn
systemLoggingOn.description: Setting this value to (1) will enable logging (via standard SYSLOG) of system messages. Setting this value to (0) will disable system logging.

systemLogNumber.name: systemLogNumber
systemLogNumber.description: The log number (0-7 of standard SYSLOG) for system logging.

systemLogFilter.name: systemLogFilter
systemLogFilter.description: Select the filter level for SYSTEM Logs Available settings: Emergency(0), Alert(1), Critical(2), Error(3), Warning(4), Notice(5), Info(6), Debug(7)

systemLogServerIp.name: systemLogServerIp
systemLogServerIp.description: IP address of the SYSLOG server to receive system messages.

systemSaveToFile.name: systemSaveToFile
systemSaveToFile.description: Setting this value to (1) will enable saving of SYSTEM logs to file. Setting this value to (0) will disable storing of SYSTEM logs in a file.

systemReportLoggingOn.name: systemReportLoggingOn
systemReportLoggingOn.description: Setting this value to (1) will enable logging (via standard SYSLOG) of SYSTEM REPORT messages. Setting this value to (0) will disable SYSTEM REPORT logging.

systemReportLogNumber.name: systemReportLogNumber
systemReportLogNumber.description: The log number (0-7 of standard SYSLOG) for SYSTEM REPORT logging.

systemReportLogServerIp.name: systemReportLogServerIp
systemReportLogServerIp.description: IP address of the SYSLOG server to receive SYSTEM REPORT log messages.

systemReportLogInterval.name: systemReportLogInterval
systemReportLogInterval.description: Interval (in minutes) with which SYSTEM REPORT log messages are sent

systemVersion.name: systemVersion
systemVersion.description: Version of the unit, includes model and software version.

systemReboot.name: systemReboot
systemReboot.description: Setting this value to (1) will cause the operating system to reboot.

systemBridgeMode.name: systemBridgeMode
systemBridgeMode.description: Setting this value to (1) will enable bridge mode. Setting this value to (0) will disable bridge mode. Note: If trying to set this value returns an error, please check to see if you have a valid license for this feature.

systemConfigFile.name: systemConfigFile
systemConfigFile.description: Setting this value to (1) will restore the factory configuration settings. Setting this value to (2) will export the current configuration to an archive file. Setting this value to (3) will restore settings from the most recent archive file, if one exists.

systemConfigFileStatus.name: systemConfigFileStatus
systemConfigFileStatus.description: This value indicates the status of systemConfigFile set query. (0) - no error occurred, (1) - error occurred, current settings were not changed, (2) - error occurred, current settings may have been corrupted, (3) - error occurred, current settings were not archived.

systemAdminConcurrencyOn.name: systemAdminConcurrencyOn
systemAdminConcurrencyOn.description: Setting this value to (1) will enable Admin Interface Concurrency enforcement. Setting this value to (0) will disable Concurrency enforcement. Note: If trying to set this value returns an error, please check to see if you have a valid license for this feature.

systemHistoryTable.name: systemHistoryTable
systemHistoryTable.description: List of last 500 access/reboot history entries.

systemHistoryLogin.name: systemHistoryLogin
systemHistoryLogin.description: Login name of the user who generated access.

systemHistoryAddress.name: systemHistoryAddress
systemHistoryAddress.description: IP Address of the machine from which access was made.

systemSyslogAddress.name: systemSyslogAddress
systemSyslogAddress.description: IP Address of the machine which send the syslog.

systemStaticPortMappingTable.name: systemStaticPortMappingTable
systemStaticPortMappingTable.description: List of Static Port-mapping Table entries.

systemStaticPortMappingMAC.name: systemStaticPortMappingMAC
systemStaticPortMappingMAC.description: Physical Address of the subscriber/device entered in one of the formats: 001122334455, 00-11-22-33-44-55 or 00:11:22:33:44:55. Default value is 00:00:00:00:00:00 .

systemStaticPortMappingExternalIP.name: systemStaticPortMappingExternalIP
systemStaticPortMappingExternalIP.description: IP Address of the NSE subscriber side (DAT IP).

systemStaticPortMappingRemoteIP.name: systemStaticPortMappingRemoteIP
systemStaticPortMappingRemoteIP.description: (OPTIONAL) IP Address of the network side machine.

systemStaticPortMappingRemotePort.name: systemStaticPortMappingRemotePort
systemStaticPortMappingRemotePort.description: (OPTIONAL) Remote Port (of the network side machine)

systemStaticPortMappingStatus.name: systemStaticPortMappingStatus
systemStaticPortMappingStatus.description: Status of the Static Port-mapping table entry.

blockIcmpFromPending.name: blockIcmpFromPending
blockIcmpFromPending.description: Set to 1 to enable blocking ICMP packets from pending subscribers.

timeOffsetSign.name: timeOffsetSign
timeOffsetSign.description: Offset sign for time offset (+/- hh:mm) from UTC. Note: you must reboot for changes to take effect.

timeOffsetHours.name: timeOffsetHours
timeOffsetHours.description: Hours offset for time offset (+/- hh:mm) from UTC. Note: you must reboot for changes to take effect.

timeOffsetMinutes.name: timeOffsetMinutes
timeOffsetMinutes.description: Minutes offset for time offset (+/- hh:mm) from UTC. Note: you must reboot for changes to take effect.

timeServerTimeout.name: timeServerTimeout
timeServerTimeout.description: Time server timeout in seconds. Note: you must reboot for changes to take effect.

timeServer1.name: timeServer1
timeServer1.description: IP address or DNS name of the first time server. Note: you must reboot for changes to take effect.

timeServer2.name: timeServer2
timeServer2.description: IP address or DNS name of the second time server. Note: you must reboot for changes to take effect.

timeServer3.name: timeServer3
timeServer3.description: IP address or DNS name of the third time server. Note: you must reboot for changes to take effect.

timeServer4.name: timeServer4
timeServer4.description: IP address or DNS name of the fourth time server. Note: you must reboot for changes to take effect.

urlFilteringOn.name: urlFilteringOn
urlFilteringOn.description: Setting this value to (1) will enable URL Filtering feature. Setting this value to (0) will disable it.

urlFilteringIPTable.name: urlFilteringIPTable
urlFilteringIPTable.description: Table of IP addresses that will be filtered.

urlFilteringIPTableAddress.name: urlFilteringIPTableAddress
urlFilteringIPTableAddress.description: IP address traffic to which will be blocked.

urlFilteringDNSTable.name: urlFilteringDNSTable
urlFilteringDNSTable.description: Table of DNS names or Domain names that will be filtered.

urlFilteringDNSTableName.name: urlFilteringDNSTableName
urlFilteringDNSTableName.description: DNS name or Domain name traffic to which will be blocked.

urlFilteringDNSTableStatus.name: urlFilteringDNSTableStatus
urlFilteringDNSTableStatus.description: Status of the URL Filtering DNS table entry.

macFilteringOn.name: macFilteringOn
macFilteringOn.description: Setting this value to (1) will enable the MAC Filtering feature. Setting this value to (0) will disable it.

macFilteringTable.name: macFilteringTable
macFilteringTable.description: Table of MAC addresses that will be filtered.

macFilteringTableAddress.name: macFilteringTableAddress
macFilteringTableAddress.description: MAC address traffic to be filtered.

macFilteringStatus.name: macFilteringStatus
macFilteringStatus.description: Status of the MAC Filter Table Entry.

tunnelingOn.name: tunnelingOn
tunnelingOn.description: Setting this value to (1) will enable tunneling. Setting this value to (0) will disable it.

wirelessSsid.name: wirelessSsid
wirelessSsid.description: Default SSID of the AG. Note: you must reboot for changes to take effect.

wirelessSsidBroadcastOn.name: wirelessSsidBroadcastOn
wirelessSsidBroadcastOn.description: Setting this value to (1) will enable Default SSID Broadcast. Setting this value to (0) will disable it. Note: you must reboot for changes to take effect.

wirelessChannel.name: wirelessChannel
wirelessChannel.description: Channel number for the wireless interface. Setting it to zero will enable auto channel configuration. Note: not all of the channels might be available depending on the regulatory domain and type of wireless interface (b/g or a). Note: you must reboot for changes to take effect.

wirelessRate.name: wirelessRate
wirelessRate.description: Data rate for the wireless interface. Note: not all of the rates might be available depending on type of wireless interface (b/g or a). Note: you must reboot for changes to take effect.

wirelessPower.name: wirelessPower
wirelessPower.description: Level of transmit power for the wireless interface. Note: you must reboot for changes to take effect.

wirelessFragLength.name: wirelessFragLength
wirelessFragLength.description: Fragment length. Note: you must reboot for changes to take effect.

wirelessRtsLength.name: wirelessRtsLength
wirelessRtsLength.description: RTS length. Note: you must reboot for changes to take effect.

wirelessBeaconInterval.name: wirelessBeaconInterval
wirelessBeaconInterval.description: Beacon interval. Note: you must reboot for changes to take effect.

wirelessDtim.name: wirelessDtim
wirelessDtim.description: Delivery Traffic Indication Message (DTIM). Note: you must reboot for changes to take effect.

wirelessShortPreambleOn.name: wirelessShortPreambleOn
wirelessShortPreambleOn.description: Setting this value to (1) will enable short preamble. Setting this value to (0) will disable it. Note: you must reboot for changes to take effect.

wirelessMssidVlanOn.name: wirelessMssidVlanOn
wirelessMssidVlanOn.description: Set to 1 to enable, 0 to disable SSID based WAN VLAN. Note: enabling SSID based WAN VLAN will automatically disable RADIUS based WAN VLAN.

wirelessMssidVlanDefaultOn.name: wirelessMssidVlanDefaultOn
wirelessMssidVlanDefaultOn.description: Set to 1 to enable default 802.1q tag for system traffic, 0 to disable.

wirelessMssidVlanDefaultTag.name: wirelessMssidVlanDefaultTag
wirelessMssidVlanDefaultTag.description: Set the default 802.1q tag for system traffic.

mssidName.name: mssidName
mssidName.description: SSID name. Note: you must reboot for changes to take effect.

mssidVlan.name: mssidVlan
mssidVlan.description: SSID VLAN. Note: you must reboot for changes to take effect.

mssidStatus.name: mssidStatus
mssidStatus.description: Status of the Multiple SSID table entry.

wirelessWepOn.name: wirelessWepOn
wirelessWepOn.description: Setting this value to (1) will enable WEP. Setting this value to (0) will disable it. Note: you must reboot for changes to take effect.

wirelessWepClients.name: wirelessWepClients
wirelessWepClients.description: Type of clients supported by AG.

wirelessWepAuthType.name: wirelessWepAuthType
wirelessWepAuthType.description: Setting this value to (0) will set 802.11 authentication type to open. Setting this value to (1) will set it to shared. Note: you must reboot for changes to take effect.

wirelessWepNon1xAllowedOn.name: wirelessWepNon1xAllowedOn
wirelessWepNon1xAllowedOn.description: Setting this value to (1) will allow access for non-802.1x clients. Setting this value to (0) will disallow it. Note: you must reboot for changes to take effect.

wirelessWepKeyType.name: wirelessWepKeyType
wirelessWepKeyType.description: Type of the WEP key: Hexadecimal digits or ASCII characters. Note: you must reboot for changes to take effect.

wirelessWepDefaultKey.name: wirelessWepDefaultKey
wirelessWepDefaultKey.description: Default WEP Key. Index of a WEP key which will be used to encrypt all transmitted and received frames for the stations which do not have a private key associated with them. Note: you must reboot for changes to take effect.

wirelessWepKey1.name: wirelessWepKey1
wirelessWepKey1.description: WEP Key 1. Note: make sure that key length is correct depending on the key type: Ascii 64-bit key - 5 characters long Ascii 128-bit key - 13 characters long Ascii 152-bit key - 16 characters long Hex 64-bit key - 10 hex digits long Hex 128-bit key - 26 hex digits long Hex 152-bit key - 32 hex digits long Note: you must reboot for changes to take effect.

wirelessWepKey2.name: wirelessWepKey2
wirelessWepKey2.description: WEP Key 2. Note: make sure that key length is correct depending on the key type: Ascii 64-bit key - 5 characters long Ascii 128-bit key - 13 characters long Ascii 152-bit key - 16 characters long Hex 64-bit key - 10 hex digits long Hex 128-bit key - 26 hex digits long Hex 152-bit key - 32 hex digits long Note: you must reboot for changes to take effect.

wirelessWepKey3.name: wirelessWepKey3
wirelessWepKey3.description: WEP Key 3. Note: make sure that key length is correct depending on the key type: Ascii 64-bit key - 5 characters long Ascii 128-bit key - 13 characters long Ascii 152-bit key - 16 characters long Hex 64-bit key - 10 hex digits long Hex 128-bit key - 26 hex digits long Hex 152-bit key - 32 hex digits long Note: you must reboot for changes to take effect.

wirelessWepKey4.name: wirelessWepKey4
wirelessWepKey4.description: WEP Key 4. Note: make sure that key length is correct depending on the key type: Ascii 64-bit key - 5 characters long Ascii 128-bit key - 13 characters long Ascii 152-bit key - 16 characters long Hex 64-bit key - 10 hex digits long Hex 128-bit key - 26 hex digits long Hex 152-bit key - 32 hex digits long Note: you must reboot for changes to take effect.

nseRadCapacityReached.name: nseRadCapacityReached
nseRadCapacityReached.description: This trap is generated when the limit of Radius caching file is reached.

pppoeSvcName.name: pppoeSvcName
pppoeSvcName.description: Servicename that will be requested of the PPPoE client. Blank means any service is acceptable.

pppEchoReqIntvl.name: pppEchoReqIntvl
pppEchoReqIntvl.description: Frequency in seconds that LCP echo requests will be sent to the server.

pppEchoMaxNonresp.name: pppEchoMaxNonresp
pppEchoMaxNonresp.description: Maximum number of echo requests that can go unresponded to before the PPP link is considered to be down.

pppAuthUsername.name: pppAuthUsername
pppAuthUsername.description: Username to be used during authentication phase of establishing PPP link. Used for PAP or CHAP.

pppAuthPassword.name: pppAuthPassword
pppAuthPassword.description: Password/Secret to be used during authentication phase of establishing PPP link. Used for PAP or CHAP.

pppIpCfgMode.name: pppIpCfgMode
pppIpCfgMode.description: Decides whether to request an IP address from the server (dynamic) or inform the server of the desired IP address (static)

pppStaticIpAddr.name: pppStaticIpAddr
pppStaticIpAddr.description: If pppIpCfgMode is set to static, this is the IP address that will be used.

pppMaxTcpMss.name: pppMaxTcpMss
pppMaxTcpMss.description: Specifies the maximum TCP MSS option value to use for subscriber TCP connections across the PPP network interface. The actual value used may be less than the configured value if necessary based on the MTU of the PPP interface. Values above 1952 are not allowed.

localWebPagesTable.name: localWebPagesTable
localWebPagesTable.description: Table of local Web page names.

localWebPagesTableStatus.name: localWebPagesTableStatus
localWebPagesTableStatus.description: Status of the Local Web pages table entry.

localWebImagesTable.name: localWebImagesTable
localWebImagesTable.description: Table of local Web image names.

localWebImagesTableStatus.name: localWebImagesTableStatus
localWebImagesTableStatus.description: Status of local Web images table entry.

ipsecVpnOn.name: ipsecVpnOn
ipsecVpnOn.description: Setting this value to (1) enables IPSec over the network interface. Setting it to zero disables it. Valid license is required. When this variable is changed, system must be rebooted for the change to take effect. (NOTE: This is not to be confused with the MIB variable ipsecOn, which pertains to the passthru of IPSec traffic to/from a subscriber host.)

ipsecPeerTableEntry.name: ipsecPeerTableEntry
ipsecPeerTableEntry.description: Parameters for a specific IPSec peer.

ipsecPeerIpAddr.name: ipsecPeerIpAddr
ipsecPeerIpAddr.description: IP Address of the IPSec peer.

ipsecPeerAuthMethod.name: ipsecPeerAuthMethod
ipsecPeerAuthMethod.description: Method to be used to authenticate and be authenticated by IPSec peer

ipsecPeerSharedKey.name: ipsecPeerSharedKey
ipsecPeerSharedKey.description: The key to be used if ipsecPeerAuthMethod is preSharedKey.

ipsecPeerPrivkeyFile.name: ipsecPeerPrivkeyFile
ipsecPeerPrivkeyFile.description: The filename (within the /flash/ipseccrt directory) of the file containing the private key to be used for X509 authentication. Only needed if ipsecPeerAuthMethod is x509Certificate

ipsecPeerCertFile.name: ipsecPeerCertFile
ipsecPeerCertFile.description: The filename (within the /flash/ipseccrt directory) of the file containing the X.509 certificate to be used for X509 authentication. Only needed if ipsecPeerAuthMethod is x509Certificate

ipsecPeerEncDesOk.name: ipsecPeerEncDesOk
ipsecPeerEncDesOk.description: Indicates whether DES encryption is allowed to be used on the IKE channel between the NSE and this peer.

ipsecPeerEnc3DesOk.name: ipsecPeerEnc3DesOk
ipsecPeerEnc3DesOk.description: Indicates whether 3DES encryption is allowed to be used on the IKE channel between the NSE and this peer.

ipsecPeerHashMd5Ok.name: ipsecPeerHashMd5Ok
ipsecPeerHashMd5Ok.description: Indicates whether MD5 hashing is allowed to be used on the IKE channel between the NSE and this peer.

ipsecPeerHashShaOk.name: ipsecPeerHashShaOk
ipsecPeerHashShaOk.description: Indicates whether SHA hashing is allowed to be used on the IKE channel between the NSE and this peer.

ipsecPeerKeyStrength.name: ipsecPeerKeyStrength
ipsecPeerKeyStrength.description: The key strength to be used on the IKE channel between the NSE and this peer

ipsecPeerLifetime.name: ipsecPeerLifetime
ipsecPeerLifetime.description: The lifetime (in seconds) of the IKE channel between the NSE and this peer, before it needs to be torn down and re-established.

ipsecPeerStatus.name: ipsecPeerStatus
ipsecPeerStatus.description: Status of the IPSec peer table entry.

ipsecPolicyTableEntry.name: ipsecPolicyTableEntry
ipsecPolicyTableEntry.description: Parameters for a specific IPSec security policy.

ipsecPolicyPeerIp.name: ipsecPolicyPeerIp
ipsecPolicyPeerIp.description: IP Address of the IPSec peer for this policy. There must be an entry in the peer table for this peer

ipsecPolicyProtocol.name: ipsecPolicyProtocol
ipsecPolicyProtocol.description: The IP protocol number (e.g. 6 for TCP) of the protocol this policy pertains to. a zero means it pertains to ANY protocol.

ipsecPolicyRemIp.name: ipsecPolicyRemIp
ipsecPolicyRemIp.description: IP Address of the remote host/subnet to which this policy pertains.

ipsecPolicyRemSubnet.name: ipsecPolicyRemSubnet
ipsecPolicyRemSubnet.description: Subnet mask of the remote subnet to which this policy pertains.

ipsecPolicyRemPort.name: ipsecPolicyRemPort
ipsecPolicyRemPort.description: The remote TCP/UDP port number to which this policy pertains. A zero means it pertains to ANY port number. This field is only used if the protocol number is 6 (TCP) or 17 (UDP).

ipsecPolicyUseNetIp.name: ipsecPolicyUseNetIp
ipsecPolicyUseNetIp.description: Indicates whether or not this policy pertains to traffic originated by and/or destined to the NSE's network interface IP address. Otherwise it would pertain to a device on the subscriber network.

ipsecPolicyLocIp.name: ipsecPolicyLocIp
ipsecPolicyLocIp.description: If ipsecPolicyUseNetIp is no, this is the IP Address of the subscriber-side host/subnet to which this policy pertains.

ipsecPolicyLocSubnet.name: ipsecPolicyLocSubnet
ipsecPolicyLocSubnet.description: If ipsecPolicyUseNetIp is no, this is the Subnet mask of the subscriber-side subnet to which this policy pertains.

ipsecPolicyLocPort.name: ipsecPolicyLocPort
ipsecPolicyLocPort.description: The local TCP/UDP port number to which this policy pertains. A zero means it pertains to ANY port number. This field is only used if the protocol number is 6 (TCP) or 17 (UDP).

ipsecPolicyType.name: ipsecPolicyType
ipsecPolicyType.description: The type of IPSec security policy this is, i.e., what type of action to take on packets that fit the traffic selectors.

ipsecPolicyDirType.name: ipsecPolicyDirType
ipsecPolicyDirType.description: The traffic direction to which this policy pertains. Used only for discard or bypass policies (ESP and AH tunnels always pertain to both directions)

ipsecPolicyEncDesOk.name: ipsecPolicyEncDesOk
ipsecPolicyEncDesOk.description: Indicates whether DES encryption is allowed to be used on the security association based on this policy. Pertains only to ESP tunnels.

ipsecPolicyEnc3desOk.name: ipsecPolicyEnc3desOk
ipsecPolicyEnc3desOk.description: Indicates whether 3DES encryption is allowed to be used on the security association based on this policy. Pertains only to ESP tunnels.

ipsecPolicyEncNullOk.name: ipsecPolicyEncNullOk
ipsecPolicyEncNullOk.description: Indicates whether NULL encryption (i.e., not encrypted) is allowed to be used on the security association based on this policy. Pertains only to ESP tunnels.

ipsecPolicyAuthMd5Ok.name: ipsecPolicyAuthMd5Ok
ipsecPolicyAuthMd5Ok.description: Indicates whether MD5 authentication is allowed to be used on the security association based on this policy. Pertains to both ESP and AH tunnels.

ipsecPolicyAuthShaOk.name: ipsecPolicyAuthShaOk
ipsecPolicyAuthShaOk.description: Indicates whether SHA authentication is allowed to be used on the security association based on this policy. Pertains to both ESP and AH tunnels.

ipsecPolicyAuthNullOk.name: ipsecPolicyAuthNullOk
ipsecPolicyAuthNullOk.description: Indicates whether no authentication is allowed to be used on the security association based on this policy. Pertains only to ESP tunnels.

ipsecPolicyPfsStrength.name: ipsecPolicyPfsStrength
ipsecPolicyPfsStrength.description: Indicates whether perfect forward secrecy is to be used on the security association based on this policy, and if so what lever of keying strength to use. Pertains to either ESP or AH tunnels.

ipsecPolicyMaxLifetime.name: ipsecPolicyMaxLifetime
ipsecPolicyMaxLifetime.description: The maximum lifetime (in seconds) a security association based on this policy may stay up before it must either be torn down or renewed. A zero means there is no maximum.

ipsecPolicyMaxLifesize.name: ipsecPolicyMaxLifesize
ipsecPolicyMaxLifesize.description: The maximum amount of data (in bytes) that may pass thru a tunnel based on this policy before it must either be torn down or renewed. A zero means there is no maximum.

ipsecPolicyAutoRenew.name: ipsecPolicyAutoRenew
ipsecPolicyAutoRenew.description: Indicates whether the security association based on this policy should be automatically renewed or not. Used only if either ipsecPolicyMaxLifesize or ipsecPolicyMaxLifetime is non-zero.

ipsecPolicyStatus.name: ipsecPolicyStatus
ipsecPolicyStatus.description: Status of the IPSec policy table entry.

ipsecSaStatusTable.name: ipsecSaStatusTable
ipsecSaStatusTable.description: List of the status of security associations corresponding to configured IPSec security policies.

ipsecSaStatusTableEntry.name: ipsecSaStatusTableEntry
ipsecSaStatusTableEntry.description: Information about the status of an IPSec security association.

ipsecSaStatusState.name: ipsecSaStatusState
ipsecSaStatusState.description: Indicates the state ofwhether the security association corresponding to the configured security policy is presently up or down.

ipsecSaStatusStatus.description: Status of the IPSec security association table entry.
